In my opinion, using cv::Point2f is better than x and y extracted not only here but also everywhere because it is easy to read. cv::Point_ implements useful operations such as operator + and operator -.

Please assume that you deal in Matrix 2x2. I think the following code is not a good idea.
```
c_0_0 = a_0_0 + b_0_0;
c_0_1 = a_0_1 + b_0_1;
c_1_0 = a_1_0 + b_1_0;
c_1_1 = a_1_1 + b_1_1;
```
instead of
```
c = a + b;
```

